1
00:00:01,120 --> 00:00:01,950
对不住了 圣诞老人
Sorry, Santa.

2
00:00:04,950 --> 00:00:06,330
前情提要

3
00:00:06,410 --> 00:00:10,040
是内森吗 你在干什么 孩子  一切都还好吗 
Nathaniel? What are you doin', buddy? Hey, is everything okay?

4
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:13,250
他说你不能回家过圣诞节也没关系

5
00:00:13,330 --> 00:00:16,000
我说回去 就一定回去
Hey. You know I'm gonna be there, like I said.

6
00:00:17,250 --> 00:00:19,910
所以浪人已经死了 杀掉他的人也已经死了
So Ronin is dead, and the person who killed him is dead.

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,950
死无对证啊 你怎么知道的 
That's convenient. How do you know this?

8
00:00:22,040 --> 00:00:23,120
因为我在场
'Cause I was there.

9
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:25,660
接下来的拍卖品
Up next, we have an artifact

10
00:00:25,750 --> 00:00:29,250
是来自复仇者联盟基地废墟的遗物
recovered from the wreckage of the Avengers compound.

11
00:00:29,330 --> 00:00:30,750
这块表
The lots.

12
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:36,330
纽约市的名流阿曼德·杜凯恩
New York socialite Armand Duquesne

13
00:00:36,410 --> 00:00:38,370
昨晚在他的住所被发现遇害
was found dead in his home last night.

14
00:00:38,450 --> 00:00:41,370
我是纽约市警察局的考德尔探员
This is Detective Caudie of the New York Police Department.

15
00:00:41,450 --> 00:00:43,500
毕肖普小姐 你能来警局一趟吗 
Ms. Bishop, can you come down to the station for a quick chat?

16
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:46,500
你说阿曼德是怎么死的 
How'd you say Armand was killed?

17
00:00:46,580 --> 00:00:47,790
被剑捅死的
Stabbed with a sword.

18
00:00:47,870 --> 00:00:49,370
看看有没有卡齐的信息
See if there's anything on Kazi.

19
00:00:49,450 --> 00:00:52,660
好吧 这是什么公司 斯隆有限公司  卡齐是雇员之一 
Okay, what's this company, Sloan Limited? Kazi is an employee?

20
00:00:53,410 --> 00:00:55,120
我看看能不能查到杰克
Let me see what I can pull up on Jack.

21
00:00:56,620 --> 00:00:57,910
我被强制退出了
And I've just been locked out.

22
00:00:59,290 --> 00:01:00,200
别动
Don't move.

23
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:36,080
漫威影业出品

24
00:01:40,660 --> 00:01:43,750
待在那别动
Stay exactly where you are.

25
00:01:44,410 --> 00:01:45,450
杰克 不要
Jack, no!

26
00:01:45,540 --> 00:01:47,370
这是怎么回事 
What the hell is going on?

27
00:01:48,450 --> 00:01:50,750
为什么有个复仇者在我的餐厅里 
And why is there an Avenger in my dining room?

28
00:01:51,370 --> 00:01:52,200
你好
Hi.

29
00:01:52,290 --> 00:01:55,540
天啊 你是…你是那个弓箭手
Oh, my God. You're... You're Archer.

30
00:01:55,620 --> 00:01:56,910
-鹰眼 -克林特
-Hawkeye. -Clint.

31
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,290
-我跟你说过 就是人设问题 -没错
-It's the branding issue, I'm telling you. -Yeah, sure.

32
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:06,910
《鹰眼》
第一季第四集

33
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:11,700
鹰眼和我在办案 我们需要用一下洗手间
Hawkeye and I are working on a case, and we needed to use the bathroom.

34
00:02:11,790 --> 00:02:15,080
是他要用 我们正好经过这里 就顺便进来一下 没什么大事
He did. So, we were by the house, we dropped in. No big deal.

35
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:17,330
-你们在一起办案  -真厉害啊
-Working on a case together? -How terrific.

36
00:02:18,370 --> 00:02:19,870
他是我的搭档
He's my partner.

37
00:02:19,950 --> 00:02:21,250
我们不是搭档
We're not partners.

38
00:02:21,330 --> 00:02:23,790
我们算是朋友兼搭档
Well, we're friends-slash-partners.

39
00:02:23,870 --> 00:02:25,950
我也不觉得咱们是朋友
I wouldn't really describe us as friends.

40
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:32,910
十分钟前有人用我的笔记本 登陆了我的工作帐户
Someone used my laptop to sign onto my work account ten minutes ago.

41
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,580
你知道怎么回事吗 凯特 
Any thoughts, Kate?

42
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,410
鹰眼 
Hawkeye?

43
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:42,700
他什么都不会说的 神箭手不善于与人交流
You'll never get anything outta him. See, CB-One has trouble opening up.

44
00:02:42,790 --> 00:02:44,120
从来没人叫我神箭手
Nobody calls me CB-One.

45
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:45,700
我就试着叫一下
I'm just tryin' it out for a second.

46
00:02:45,790 --> 00:02:49,410
可能是有什么童年阴影 他觉得没和我说过什么
Probably some early childhood thing. He thinks he doesn't tell me much,

47
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,450
-其实他和我说了很多 -我什么都没和她说过
-but he ends up telling me all of it. -I tell her nothing.

48
00:02:51,540 --> 00:02:53,910
我觉得可能是因为我比较冷静
I think it's 'cause I'm generally pretty chill.

49
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,950
我不会像其他人那样大呼小叫 〝天啊 是鹰眼〟
I'm not like, "Oh, my God, Hawkeye!"

50
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:58,250
你可一点都不冷静
Definitely not chill.

51
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,370
我插一句 谢谢你…拯救了世界
By the way, thank you... for saving the world.

52
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:06,790
不用谢
Don't mention it.

53
00:03:06,910 --> 00:03:09,830
我想听我女儿跟我说实话
I would like my daughter to start telling me the truth.

54
00:03:11,450 --> 00:03:14,410
是我登录了你的帐户 因为我需要信息
I logged into your account because I needed information

55
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:18,870
案子是真的 人是真的 他们身处的险境也是真的
on an actual case with actual people who are in actual danger.

56
00:03:18,950 --> 00:03:22,910
所以 凯特在帮你处理 复仇者级别的威胁 
So, Kate is helping you with an Avengers-level threat?

57
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,410
也不算是吧
Well, not exactly.

58
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:26,160
但是你们在一起合作 
But you are working together?

59
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:35,580
对 听着有点奇怪 确实奇怪
Yes. Sounds weird, 'cause it is.

60
00:03:37,870 --> 00:03:39,160
好吧
Okay.

61
00:03:40,290 --> 00:03:44,910
好吧 看来我得相信 大家都在做正确的事
Well, I guess I'm just gonna have to trust everyone at this table to do what's right.

62
00:03:48,290 --> 00:03:50,370
好的 很高兴见到你们
Cool. It was great bumpin' into you guys.

63
00:03:50,450 --> 00:03:51,950
-你别走 -我们得走了…
-Please stay. -We should get...

64
00:03:55,290 --> 00:03:56,330
我能送你出去吗 
Can I see you out?

65
00:03:57,250 --> 00:03:58,910
我去拿外衣 杰克 再见
I'll get my coat. Jack.

66
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:15,950
我得说清楚
Let me clarify.

67
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:16,910
好
Yeah.

68
00:04:18,330 --> 00:04:20,080
她可不是什么超级英雄
She is not a superhero.

69
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:22,450
是的 我当然知道
Oh, yeah. Come on, I already knew that.

70
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:24,830
她身手不错 但是…
She's pretty good at all this, but...

71
00:04:24,910 --> 00:04:27,790
娜塔莎·罗曼诺夫身手也不错 对吗 
Natasha Romanoff was pretty damn good at it, wasn't she?

72
00:04:29,910 --> 00:04:32,540
身手不错也不一定能保命
Being good isn't always enough to keep you alive.

73
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,000
我知道了
I see.

74
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:38,120
-克林特  -怎么 
-Clint? -Yeah?

75
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,200
你有孩子吗 
Do you have kids?

76
00:04:40,330 --> 00:04:42,080
我就当你有
Yeah, I'm gonna assume that you do.

77
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:45,290
这一周对我们家而言很煎熬
It's been a rough week for my family.

78
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:50,160
但是我必须告诉你 我不能失去凯特
But I am letting you know that I cannot lose Kate.

79
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:55,040
我以前失去过亲人 我知道你也有过类似的经历
I've lost people before. I know in your line of work, you have, too.

80
00:04:56,790 --> 00:04:59,200
我明白 好的
I understand. Okay.

81
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,580
所以你会放弃这个案子 
So, you'll forget this case?

82
00:05:04,330 --> 00:05:05,580
这可不行
I can't do that.

83
00:05:06,370 --> 00:05:09,950
但是我可以保证的是 你女儿一定会安然无恙 好吗 
But what I can do is ensure that your daughter stays safe. Okay?

84
00:05:23,250 --> 00:05:30,200
劳拉 帮我查一下〝斯隆有限公司〟好吗

85
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:41,410
我是埃莉诺
It's Eleanor. Um...

86
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:46,040
能不能给我回个电话 情况紧急
Could you call me back, please? It's urgent.

87
00:05:48,790 --> 00:05:50,660
你发现什么了吗 
Hey. Did you find anything?

88
00:05:51,370 --> 00:05:55,000
我和你那个朋友聊过了 他很忙
I talked to that friend of yours. He's really busy.

89
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:58,410
他一边学俄语 一边还要不停锻炼
He's been learning Russian and jogging a ton.

90
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:01,540
运动服黑帮 斯隆是他们的幌子 
Tracksuits. So Sloan is their front?

91
00:06:01,620 --> 00:06:05,540
对 他说他的老板杰克·杜凯恩 从来不让他休息
Yep. He said that his boss, Jack Duquesne, never gives him a day off.

92
00:06:05,620 --> 00:06:09,160
杰克是CEO  他在给他们的老大洗钱 
Jack's CEO? He's laundering money for the big guy?

93
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:11,410
我觉得你可能还得多待一天
Let me guess, you're gonna need another day.

94
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:15,620
是这样 我救了个孩子 她被卷进来了
Yeah, look, uh, this kid I'm helping is stuck in the middle of it,

95
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:17,450
我得保证她安全以后才能走
so I can't leave until I know she's safe.

96
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,410
我一直在想…
I've been wondering...

97
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:21,450
基地里还有什么东西不见了吗

98
00:06:21,540 --> 00:06:22,870
你是说劳力士 
You mean the Rolex?

99
00:06:23,330 --> 00:06:24,160
没错

100
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:25,830
是爸爸
It's Dad.

101
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:30,540
不会吧…我觉得不会吧
I don't think... I don't think so.

102
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:35,200
为什么提起这个  那不是好几年前就毁掉了吗 
Why? Wasn't that destroyed, like, years ago?

103
00:06:35,290 --> 00:06:38,950
我也这么觉得 但是你那件炫酷的战服不也一样嘛
Well, I thought so, but I thought the same thing about your fancy outfit.

104
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,790
看来得调查一下 对吗 
It's worth lookin' into, ain't it?

105
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:45,540
如果可以的话 查一下发射器的信号
If you can, check the signal from the transmitter.

106
00:06:45,620 --> 00:06:48,700
好的 你说话怎么气喘吁吁的 你累了 
Okay. You sound like you've been runnin' around all day. Are you tired?

107
00:06:48,790 --> 00:06:51,540
是的 我受了点小伤 但是没大事
Yeah, I'm a little banged up, but nothing's broken.

108
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:53,830
好吧 放松一下
Okay. Well, put your feet up.

109
00:06:53,910 --> 00:06:57,160
有必要就冰敷一下 好吗 我爱你
Ice them if you have to. Okay? I love you.

110
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,700
我…我很想你
I... I miss you.

111
00:07:00,370 --> 00:07:02,450
我尽快回去 我保证
I'll see you soon. I promise.

112
00:07:02,540 --> 00:07:03,540
再见
Bye.

113
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:08,410
孩子们 看来爸爸还得再忙一阵
Uh, guys, looks like Dad's gonna be stuck at work a little longer.

114
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:16,950
她非常痴迷于克林特·巴顿 自从…
Obsessed. Completely obsessed with Clint Barton since...

115
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,250
自从那次袭击以后
Well, ever since the attack.

116
00:07:19,330 --> 00:07:21,870
她在偶像面前表现得还挺镇定
She's awfully composed around her own idol.

117
00:07:21,950 --> 00:07:24,410
如果能见到休伊·路易斯 我肯定疯了
If I ever met Huey Lewis, I'd be a wreck.

118
00:07:25,450 --> 00:07:27,370
凯特一直都很自信
Kate's always been confident,

119
00:07:27,450 --> 00:07:29,910
这方面她倒从来没让我担心过
never had to worry about her on that front.

120
00:07:34,330 --> 00:07:37,910
你又开始头疼了吧 亲爱的 我给你泡点茶
You're getting that pre-headache look, darling. Let me get you some tea.

121
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:40,540
你想吃点什么吗 凯特 
Would you like something, Kate?

122
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,540
不用了 谢谢
No. Thanks.

123
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,160
妈妈 我真的得和你谈谈杰克的事
Mom, I really need to talk to you about Jack.

124
00:07:49,250 --> 00:07:51,450
咱们能不能…换个话题 
Hey, could we... Um... Could we change the subject?

125
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,250
先别管他的事了 来吧
You need to give him a break. Come on.

126
00:07:54,330 --> 00:07:58,580
我需要你帮我决定 毕肖普节日聚会的事
I... I need your help with a few decisions on the Bishop holiday party.

127
00:07:58,660 --> 00:08:01,040
我觉得…我现在没那个心情
I don't... I don't think I'm in the mood.

128
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:03,540
来吧 凯特 这种事你最擅长了
Come on, Kate. You're great at this sort of thing.

129
00:08:04,950 --> 00:08:06,370
这个聚会不强制宗教信仰
The party's non-denominational,

130
00:08:06,450 --> 00:08:09,500
就是过节了 让大家增进一下感情
encourages company camaraderie with a festive spirit.

131
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,910
那还真挺有意思的
Sounds like a blast already.

132
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,000
你们是在聊聚会吗 
Did someone say parties?

133
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:17,500
一定要有跳舞环节啊
Just make sure there's plenty of dancing.

134
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:19,120
我妈妈从来不跳舞
Well, my mother doesn't dance.

135
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:24,040
真的吗 我看未必 亲爱的 
Oh, really? I beg to differ. Darling?

136
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:30,450
篝火上的板栗飘香
Chestnuts roasting on an open fire

137
00:08:33,330 --> 00:08:36,370
北风吹拂刺骨冰霜
Jack Frost nippin' at your ear

138
00:08:41,450 --> 00:08:46,410
这句祝福被反复吟唱
And though it's been said many times, many ways

139
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:53,410
祝你圣诞快乐
Merry Christmas to you

140
00:08:54,290 --> 00:08:56,330
我以前从来没见过你这样
Don't think I've ever seen you like that before.

141
00:09:00,450 --> 00:09:04,450
超级英雄登门拜访 再加上一支小夜曲 这一天真够热闹的
A superhero house call and a serenade, all in one day.

142
00:09:04,540 --> 00:09:07,870
人们常说 人生苦短
Well, you know what they say... life is short.

143
00:09:08,830 --> 00:09:10,700
你永远不知道会得到什么
You never know what you're gonna get.

144
00:09:14,620 --> 00:09:19,000
怎么了 我说什么了  我是说错了吗…
What? What'd I say? Did I say something wrong or...

145
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:23,660
这些心灵鸡汤从你嘴里说出来就没对过
Every time you use one of those aphorisms, they are... wrong.

146
00:09:24,580 --> 00:09:29,870
什么 不可能吧 亲爱的 拜托
What? No. That can't be right, is it? Darling. Please.

147
00:09:30,580 --> 00:09:35,580
那天你还说 〝小别催人老〟
The other day, you said, "Absence makes the heart grow older."

148
00:09:35,660 --> 00:09:38,290
事实就是如此啊
Because that's what it does.

149
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:42,660
-亲爱的 过来 -是吗 
- Yeah. Honey. Come here. - No. Really?

150
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:45,290
你可真是催我老了
Aw. You're making my heart grow older.

151
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:53,540
我觉得被家人笑话
I guess getting laughed at by family

152
00:09:53,620 --> 00:09:56,660
总比过节一个人孤零零的好吧 
is better than being alone in the holidays, right?

153
00:09:56,750 --> 00:10:01,450
还有什么比家人团聚更开心的呢  你们都在这里 我真高兴
What's better than being with family? I'm so glad you're both here.

154
00:10:09,290 --> 00:10:11,450
咱们玩桌游吧
You know, we should play a board game.

155
00:10:11,540 --> 00:10:12,830
这主意不错
That's a cute idea.

156
00:10:12,910 --> 00:10:15,290
有好多种可以玩呢
Risk, Yahtzee, Stratego.

157
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:53,450
是我 我带来了披萨和节日的祝福 给我开门
It's me. I come bearing pizza and holiday cheer. Let me in.

158
00:10:56,870 --> 00:10:59,250
来吧 披萨狗 好吧
Come on, Pizza Do... Okay.

159
00:11:00,830 --> 00:11:02,540
-你好 -你好
-Hey! -Hey.

160
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:05,330
-帮个忙  -出去
-A little help? -Hey, get outta there.

161
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:09,370
这可是我们期待已久的 鹰眼经典战服
All right, this is the classic Hawkeye costume we've been waitin' for.

162
00:11:09,450 --> 00:11:10,620
你这是要干什么 
What is all this?

163
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:14,700
我这是在拯救你的节日
This is me saving the holidays.

164
00:11:14,790 --> 00:11:15,790
是吗 
Is that right?

165
00:11:15,870 --> 00:11:17,830
我得让你在圣诞节前赶回家去
I'll get you home in time for the big day.

166
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:20,250
我觉得现在咱们可以先庆祝一下
Figured in the meantime, we could celebrate.

167
